messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /requests/pending

- All HTTP methods acceptable: No

- HEAD acceptable: No (not explicitly mapped in code)

- POST acceptable: No

- OPTIONS acceptable: No (not explicitly mapped in code)

- TRACE acceptable: No

- GET acceptable: Yes

- PUT acceptable: No

- DELETE acceptable: No

- PATCH acceptable: No

Explanation:
- The controller method handling this endpoint is annotated with:
  @RequestMapping(value = "/requests/pending", method = RequestMethod.GET)
  which defines the exact path "/requests/pending" and explicitly allows the GET method.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping in this controller, so the method-level path is the full path (no additional prefix in this file).
- Only the GET method is explicitly declared in the code. Per your instruction to base acceptability on the code (not runtime framework behavior), other HTTP methods (HEAD, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, OPTIONS, TRACE) are not considered acceptable because they are not explicitly mapped.
- The method is also annotated with @Secured({"ROLE_ADMIN"}), so it requires admin authority, but that does not change which HTTP methods are mapped.
